Aim : To bring up REST services using c++
===   using civetweb server to achieve server capability
      create a docker image fror this project
      push the docker image

component 1 - Civetweb
===========
1)git repo for civetweb : https://github.com/civetweb/civetweb
2)clone the repo
3)cd civetweb
4)make slib
5)make install-slib
6)now all the libraries(.so) will be stored in /usr/local/lib

component 2 - RestService
===========
1) git repo : https://github.com/supreetha16/RestServices.git
2) Clone the repo
3) cd RestServices
4) export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/usr/local/lib:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH
5) for local compilation
    a) gcc -o myprog CivetWeb_Example2.cpp -I <path>/civetweb/include -L/usr/local/lib -lcivetweb
    b) ./myprog
    c) try this in browser - http://localhost:8888/example
6) to create docker image
    a) sudo docker build -t supreetha16/civet_rest_service:1.0 .
7) run the docker image
    a) sudo docker run -p 8888:8888 -it resupreetha16/civet_rest_service:1.0
    b) try this in browser - http://localhost:8888/example


